[{"id":16448800,"title":"Pre-Trained Open Source Tools for Document Classification and Sentiment Analysis","allday":false,"start":"2026-06-12T09:00:00-07:00","end":"2026-06-12T11:00:00-07:00","created":"2026-02-18T15:46:41-08:00","description":"<p>In this workshop, you&rsquo;ll learn how to use pre-trained open source tools for document classification and sentiment analysis. Rather than building custom models from scratch, you&#39;ll explore how to apply existing models using libraries like Hugging Face&#39;s Transformers and SpaCy. You&rsquo;ll gain experience in working with these tools to process text data and perform classification or sentiment analysis with minimal setup. This session will show you how to effectively apply pre-trained models for text analysis tasks.</p>\n\n<p>Note: This workshop will be offered online through UCSF Zoom. You will receive an email from LibCal with room information and Zoom link prior to the start of the workshop.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><i>Accessibility: </i>UCSF welcomes all participants to our events. If you need a reasonable accommodation to participate in this event because of a disability, please contact Geoffrey Boushey by emailing geoffrey.boushey@ucsf.edu as soon as possible.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p style=\"color:#000000; font-style:normal; font-weight:400; text-align:start; white-space:normal; text-decoration:none; line-height:1.38; background-color:#ffffff; margin-bottom:16px\"><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt; font-variant-ligatures:normal; font-variant-alternates:normal; font-variant-numeric:normal; font-variant-east-asian:normal; font-variant-position:normal; font-variant-emoji:normal; white-space:pre-wrap\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial, sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#000000\"><span style=\"font-weight:700\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\"><span style=\"text-decoration:none\">Workshop Series: Data and Document Analysis with Python, SQL, and AI</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\n\n<p>This series is designed for researchers, staff, and students who want to learn Python from the ground up, focusing on data analysis, document analysis, and AI-based research. Throughout the workshops, we&rsquo;ll dive into various data types&mdash;including numerical data, health data, text, and images/videos&mdash;and explore analysis techniques like regression, classification, and sentiment analysis. We&rsquo;ll put a particular focus on text analysis, especially analyzing documents from our industry document library.</p>\n\n<p>As programming evolves, so does the way we learn it. While we&rsquo;ll introduce AI-assisted programming earlier in the series than in past workshop series, we&rsquo;ll still start with the basics. The early workshops (Intro to Python Parts 1 &amp; 2 and Intro to SQL) will use AI sparingly. As the series moves forward, we&rsquo;ll dive into topics like web APIs, text analysis, natural language processing, machine learning, regression, document analysis, and AI system interaction, with more AI-driven techniques along the way.<br />\n&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","url":{"public":"https://calendars.library.ucsf.edu/event/16448800","admin":"https://calendars.library.ucsf.edu/aevent.php?c=928&m=edit&event_id=16448800"},"location":"Virtual","campus":"Online","category":[{"id":27094,"name":"Data Science"},{"id":46333,"name":"Data Science > Programming"}],"owner":{"id":15596,"name":"Geoffrey Boushey"},"presenter":"","calendar":{"id":928,"name":"Library Events and Classes","public":"https://calendars.library.ucsf.edu/calendar/events","admin":"https://calendars.library.ucsf.edu/admin/calendar/928"},"seats":50,"registration":true,"registration_form_id":5701,"registration_series_linked":false,"has_registration_opened":true,"registration_open_at":"2026-02-18T15:46:41-08:00","has_registration_closed":false,"registration_close_at":"2026-06-11T09:00:00-07:00","physical_seats":0,"physical_seats_taken":0,"online_seats":50,"online_seats_taken":20,"seats_taken":20,"wait_list":true,"color":"#058488","featured_image":"https://d68g328n4ug0e.cloudfront.net/data/feat_img/138/928/1741982232.png","featured_image_alt_text":"","geolocation":null,"future_dates":[],"registration_cost":0,"more_info":"","setup_time":0,"teardown_time":0,"online_user_id":0,"online_meeting_id":"","online_host_url":"","online_join_url":"https://ucsf.zoom.us/j/94231871369?pwd=cwXbaOmTD8xBRQwvBC9w5FR6hbbarj.1","online_join_password":"cwXbaOmTD8xBRQwvBC9w5FR6hbbarj.1","online_provider":"external"},{"id":15916525,"title":"Needlecraft Monthly Meet-Up - June","allday":false,"start":"2026-06-12T12:00:00-07:00","end":"2026-06-12T13:00:00-07:00","created":"2025-12-05T11:07:10-08:00","description":"<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Verdana; font-size: 12px;\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><img alt=\"makers lab logo\" src=\"//s3.amazonaws.com/libapps/accounts/17525/images/MakersLabLogo-web.png\" style=\"width: 351px; height: 91px;\" /></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"color:#e74c3c;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"></span></strong></span><strong style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Calling all fans of knitting, crochet, cross-stitch, sewing, and embroidery!</strong></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\">This virtual meet-up is a chance for beginning and&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:14px;\">experienced</span><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"> UCSF crafters&nbsp;to come together and work on their projects in a fun and relaxed atmosphere. We hang, we chat, we work on&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:14px;\">fabulous&nbsp;projects, and share advice and inspiration. Join us! </span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><strong>Register below to receive the Zoom link and password. </strong>See all upcoming <a href=\"http://tiny.ucsf.edu/needlecraftmeetup\" target=\"_blank\">Needlecraft Meet-Ups</a> to save your seat today!</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\">All Makers Lab pop-ups are open to the UCSF community. </span>If you are a DPH employee, UCSF alum or retiree, please&nbsp;<a data-auth=\"NotApplicable\" href=\"https://www.library.ucsf.edu/ask-an-expert/makers-lab-support/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">contact the Makers Lab</a>&nbsp;to register for this pop-up.</span></p>\n\n<p><em>Photo from UCSF staff member Patty</em></p>\n\n<hr />\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"></span><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"></span><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><strong>Have questions about the Makers Lab?</strong> Visit the <a href=\"https://www.library.ucsf.edu/use/makerslab/\" target=\"_self\">Makers Lab webpage</a> <span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\">or <a href=\"https://www.library.ucsf.edu/ask-an-expert/makers-lab-support/\" target=\"_self\">contact us</a></span></span></span>. <span style=\"font-size:14px;\">The Makers Lab is open by appointment for UCSF teaching, learning, and research projects. Contact the <a href=\"https://www.library.ucsf.edu/ask-an-expert/makers-lab-support/\">Makers Lab</a> to schedule an appointment. </span></span></span></p>","url":{"public":"https://calendars.library.ucsf.edu/event/15916525","admin":"https://calendars.library.ucsf.edu/aevent.php?c=928&m=edit&event_id=15916525"},"location":"","campus":"Online","category":[{"id":25201,"name":"Makers Lab"},{"id":57276,"name":"Needlecraft"}],"owner":{"id":16958,"name":"UCSF Library Makers Lab"},"presenter":"Ariel Deardorff","calendar":{"id":928,"name":"Library Events and Classes","public":"https://calendars.library.ucsf.edu/calendar/events","admin":"https://calendars.library.ucsf.edu/admin/calendar/928"},"seats":12,"registration":true,"registration_form_id":16241,"registration_series_linked":false,"has_registration_opened":true,"registration_open_at":"2025-12-05T11:07:10-08:00","has_registration_closed":false,"registration_close_at":"2026-06-12T12:00:00-07:00","physical_seats":0,"physical_seats_taken":0,"online_seats":12,"online_seats_taken":6,"seats_taken":6,"wait_list":true,"color":"#EB093C","featured_image":"https://d68g328n4ug0e.cloudfront.net/data/feat_img/138/928/1764961619.jpg","featured_image_alt_text":"","geolocation":null,"future_dates":[],"registration_cost":0,"more_info":"","setup_time":0,"teardown_time":0,"online_user_id":0,"online_meeting_id":"","online_host_url":"","online_join_url":"https://ucsf.zoom.us/j/97547992565?pwd=ZmHNEuktXGHjDi7cTw7IkvL1KgyDrX.1&from=addon","online_join_password":"156180","online_provider":"external"},{"id":16753084,"title":"AI Summer Discussion Club: Keeping the human in the loop","allday":false,"start":"2026-07-08T15:00:00-07:00","end":"2026-07-08T16:00:00-07:00","created":"2026-04-17T15:23:54-07:00","description":"<p data-pm-slice=\"1 1 []\">Thinking about artificial intelligence this summer? Join our AI Summer Discussion Club in person at the FAMRI Library in Mission Bay! Each month, we will discuss 2-3 articles, videos, or news pieces about different AI topics.</p>\n\n<p>We will have tea and light snacks. Feel free to sign up for single sessions or all of them!</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Upcoming:</p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>\n\t<p><strong>July 8 @ 3pm:</strong> Keeping the human in the loop</p>\n\t</li>\n\t<li>\n\t<p><strong>August 12 @ 3pm:</strong> Are we heading for AI dystopia? (<a href=\"https://calendars.library.ucsf.edu/event/16753085\">Register</a>)</p>\n\t</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>The reading/watching commitment for this series is relatively light (15-30 min of content), and discussion questions will be shared with registrants before the session. Reading/watching assigned content in advance and taking some notes is recommended, but not required for participation.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong>More information on assigned content for this session to be announced.</strong></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<h3><strong>Accessibility</strong></h3>\n\n<p>UCSF welcomes all participants to our events. If you need a reasonable accommodation to participate in this event because of a disability, please contact Eileen Chen at eileen.chen@ucsf.edu as soon as possible.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<h3><strong>People</strong></h3>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>&nbsp;</li>\n\t<li><strong>Eileen Chen</strong> is an Education and Research Librarian. She supports literature searching, AI, and open access publishing.</li>\n\t<li><strong>Geoff Boushey </strong>is a Data Science Specialist. He teaches with Python, SQL, machine learning, and AI, with an emphasis on document, text, and media analysis.</li>\n\t<li><strong>Yea-Hung Chen</strong> is a Data Science Specialist. He provides support on R, data science, and AI to the UCSF community.</li>\n</ul>","url":{"public":"https://calendars.library.ucsf.edu/event/16753084","admin":"https://calendars.library.ucsf.edu/aevent.php?c=928&m=edit&event_id=16753084"},"location":"FAMRI Library","category":[{"id":86724,"name":"AI"},{"id":27094,"name":"Data Science"}],"owner":{"id":133839,"name":"Eileen Chen"},"presenter":"","calendar":{"id":928,"name":"Library Events and Classes","public":"https://calendars.library.ucsf.edu/calendar/events","admin":"https://calendars.library.ucsf.edu/admin/calendar/928"},"seats":50,"registration":true,"registration_form_id":0,"registration_series_linked":false,"has_registration_opened":true,"registration_open_at":"2026-04-17T15:23:54-07:00","has_registration_closed":false,"registration_close_at":"2026-07-08T15:00:00-07:00","physical_seats":50,"physical_seats_taken":18,"online_seats":0,"online_seats_taken":0,"seats_taken":18,"wait_list":false,"color":"#058488","featured_image":"","featured_image_alt_text":"","geolocation":null,"future_dates":[],"registration_cost":0,"more_info":"","setup_time"